SUMMARY: MCCT's "A Grand Night for Singing"
DESCRIPTION:A Grand Night for Singing offers a collection of the greatest
  love songs in music theatre history given to us by the incomparable writ
 ing duo\, Richard Rodgers and Oscar Hammerstein II. Featuring songs from 
 the musicals Oklahoma!\, The Sound of Music\, Carousel\, The King and I\,
  South Pacific\, Cinderella and many more! With a modern setting and pers
 pective\, MCCT's production will reveal how relevant Oscar Hammerstein II
 's words still are and how Richard Rodger's music will always make audien
 ces' imaginations soar.\n\n\nTickets at http://mcct.ludus.com
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Theatre
