SUMMARY:Weekly Lilly Library puzzle tour
DESCRIPTION:Your expert guide\, our Curator of Puzzles Andrew Rhoda (http
 s://libraries.indiana.edu/andrew-rhoda)\, will introduce you to the colle
 ction\, mechanical puzzles and the collection's donor\, Jerry Slocum. You
  will learn about the various categories of mechanical puzzles and their 
 history. You will also see highlights from the collection on exhibition i
 n the Slocum Room. In addition\, there will be a group of puzzles from th
 e collection selected by the Curator for visitors to try as part of the t
 our.  Non-flash photography is permitted\, seating is available in the Sl
 ocum Room throughout the tour\, and the building is wheelchair accessible
 . The tour generally lasts a little less than one hour and is open to all
 . No reservation or RSVP is required for this free tour - just drop in!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Your expert guide\, our Curator of Puzz
 les <a href="https://libraries.indiana.edu/andrew-rhoda">Andrew Rhoda</a>
 \, will introduce you to the collection\, mechanical puzzles and the coll
 ection's donor\, Jerry Slocum. You will learn about the various categorie
 s of mechanical puzzles and their history. You will also see highlights f
 rom the collection on exhibition in the Slocum Room. In addition\, there 
 will be a group of puzzles from the collection selected by the Curator fo
 r visitors to try as part of the tour.</p><p>  Non-flash photography is p
 ermitted\, seating is available in the Slocum Room throughout the tour\, 
