 jpg" title="Du Haocheng" srcset="https://events.iu.edu/live/image/scale/2
 x/gid/92/width/200/height/300/30293_Du_Haocheng.rev.1772466007.jpg 2x\, h
 ttps://events.iu.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/92/width/200/height/300/3029
 3_Du_Haocheng.rev.1772466007.jpg 3x" data-max-w="2134" data-max-h="3199" 
 loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></picture><p>          Tenor Haoche
 ng Du is pursuing a Doctor of Music in Voice Performance degree at the Ja
 cobs School of Music\, studying under the guidance of Heidi Grant Murphy.
  Originally from Wuhan\, China\, he completed his undergraduate and gradu
 ate studies at the Wuhan Conservatory of Music. He studied under Professo
 r Leiming He during his gradute studies\, his undergradute mentors were P
 rofessor Yongxi Chen and Lecture Jinping Li. Du has earned several accola
 des\, including being a finalist in the 2023 Hubei Regional Final of the 
 14th China Golden Bell Award for Music and the 10th Hubei Golden Bell Mus
 ic Award. He also won first place in the Bel Canto Group of the Wuhan Con
 servatory of Music Cup Competition. More recently\, he was a semifinalist
  in the 2024 China Little Golden Bell First National Vocal Arts Exhibitio
 n. At IU\, Du performed La Bohème (Rodolfo) in 2025.        </p></div></
 section><section class="lw_accordion_block"><h4 class="lw_accordion_block
 _title"><button aria-expanded="false" type="button">Theo Harrah\, Bass</b
 utton></h4><div class="lw_accordion_block_content" aria-hidden="true"><pi
 cture class="lw_image lw_image30296 lw_align_left"><source type="image/we
