 -max-w="1365" data-max-h="1365" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></p
 icture><br /><p>          Mezzo-soprano Esther Jo\, from Seoul\, South Ko
 rea\, is pursuing an Artist Diploma with a Performance Fellowship and ful
 l scholarship under the tutelage of Jane Dutton at the Jacobs School of M
 usic. She also recently completed her Performer Diploma\, which includes 
 a Performer's Certificate\, with the fellowship and scholarship. With Ind
 iana University Opera Theater\, she has portrayed the title role of Carme
 n\, Madame de la Haltière in <i>Cendrillon</i>\, La Zia Principessa in <
 i>Suor Angelica</i>\, and Olga in <i>Eugene Onegin</i>. She has also appe
 ared in opera workshops\, performing Reine Gertrude in <i>Hamlet</i>\, Gi
 ovanna Seymour in <i>Anna Bolena</i>\, and Carmen in <i>Carmen\,</i> and 
 will perform Charlotte in <i>Werther</i>. Jo was named a finalist in the 
 prestigious Georgina Joshi Foundation Graduate Fellowship Competition. Sh
 e was also selected to participate in a masterclass with Stuart Skelton. 
 She will further expand her artistic career in Europe as a Faculty-Nomina
 ted and Competition Winner participant in the Berlin Performance Program.
  This summer\, she will join Opera Maine as a Studio Artist\, covering Ge
 rtrude in <i>Roméo et Juliette</i>\, and performing Khanh in <i>Bound</i
 >. In Korea\, Jo studied under Locky Chung and Su-gil Park\, performing M
 addalena in <i>Rigoletto</i> (a coproduction of Hanyang University and th
 e Seongdong Cultural Foundation)\, Dorabella in <i>Così fan tutte</i>\, 
 and Dritte Dame in <i>Die Zauberflöte</i>\, among other roles. As an alt
 o soloist\, she has appeared in Charpentier's <i>Te Deum</i>\, Vivaldi's 
 <i>Gloria</i> in D Major\, Britten's <i>A Ceremony of Carols</i>\, and Sc
 hütz's <i>Die sieben Worte Jesu Christi am Kreuz</i>. She further refine
 d her artistry through masterclasses with Mutsumi Moteki and as a voice f
 ellow at Yewool Music Stage. Jo graduated summa cum laude with a Bachelor
  of Music from Hanyang University\, receiving multiple merit-based full s
 cholarships\, an exclusive teaching certification\, and ranking among the
  top three students in the voice department. She continued her studies in
  the Master of Music program with full scholarship and research assistant
 ship.        </p></div></section><section class="lw_accordion_block"><h4 
 class="lw_accordion_block_title"><button aria-expanded="false" type="butt
