 " data-max-h="2400" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></picture><br /
 ><p>          Originally from Los Angeles\, soprano Brittany Rose Weinsto
 ck is a Performer's Diploma student at the Indiana University Jacobs Scho
 ol of Music studying under Carol Vaness\, where she also earned her Maste
 r's degree. She earned her B.A. from Pepperdine University\, studying und
 er Louise Lofquist. This summer\, Ms. Weinstock will be a Resident Artist
  with Teatro Nuovo\, covering Zaida in <i>Il Turco in Italia </i>and stud
 y-covering Donna Anna in <i>Don Giovanni. </i>Indiana University performa
 nces include the title role in Massenet's <i>Cendrillon\, </i>Micaëla in
  <i>Carmen\,</i> and Helen in<i> The Amazing Adventures of Kavalier &amp\
 ; Clay\, </i>a co-production with the Metropolitan Opera. Previous engage
 ments include Music on Site (Contessa\, <i>Le nozze di Figaro)\, </i>Aspe
 n Music Festival (Musetta cover\, <i>La Bohème)\, </i>Central City Opera
  (Anna Maurrant cover\, <i>Street Scene)\,</i> and the Sherrill Milnes Sa
 vannah VOICE Festival. Other credits include <i>H.M.S. Pinafore </i>(Jose
 phine)\, <i>Into the Woods </i>(Jack's Mother)\, and <i>Le nozze di Figar
 o </i>(Contessa) with Pepperdine University. Brittany Rose has received r
 ecognition in competitions such as the Opera Birmingham Competition (Fina
 list)\, Camille Coloratura Awards (Semi-Finalist)\, NSAL Indiana Vocal Co
 mpetition (3rd Place)\, Carolyn Bailey Argento and Loren L. Zachary Compe
 titions (Finalist)\, and Laffont Competition (Encouragement Award). Ms. W
 einstock is also an avid scholar and a 2025-26 recipient of the Georgina 
 Joshi Travel Grant\, which allowed her to travel to Central Europe to res
 earch Jewish Music of the Holocaust.        </p></div></section><section 
