UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12122704
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/f6
 d18b89-51c9-4f8f-badc-07ef66b416edfb9a81ba-1c54-4314-bb24-1fdc5b47dc31.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Bradford Woods\n\nOur Wilderness First Aid (WFA) co
 urses will give you the skills needed to respond to medical emergencies wh
 en help is far away. This is a 2-day/16-hour course that features extensiv
 e hands-on learning opportunities. Students will walk away with a 2-year W
 FA certification from Stonehearth Open Learning Opportunities (SOLO)\, whi
 ch is one of the oldest wilderness medicine organizations in the world. St
 udents may also add on CPR modules and/or re-certify for their SOLO Wilder
 ness First Responder (WFR) certification. Courses start at $275. Cost incl
 udes course materials and lunch on Saturday and Sunday. Overnight lodging 
 from Friday&ndash\;Sunday may be available for participants on a first-com
 e\, first-serve basis. Register for the course here.
LOCATION:Bradford Woods
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12122704
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
