SUMMARY:Guest Lecture – JB Dyas\, "Living the Dream: How to Get a Job i
 n Jazz Education"
DESCRIPTION:Students\, Sign up here &gt\;JB Dyas has been a leading force
  in jazz education for more than three decades. As Vice President for Edu
 cation and Curriculum Development at the Herbie Hancock Institute of Jazz
  at UCLA\, he oversees major outreach initiatives includingJazz in Americ
 a. An Indiana Universityalumnuswith a Ph.D. in Music Education\, Dyas stu
 died with and was closely mentored by legendary jazz educator David Baker
 . He previously served as Executive Director of the Brubeck Institute and
  Director of Jazz Studies at Miami-Dade College and New World School of t
 he Arts. Dyas has presented workshops and performances worldwide and is a
 DownBeatJazz Education Achievement Award recipient.
