LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
SUMMARY:ACC's Student Development Workshop Series presents: "I am perfect
 ly FINE!: How do you balance productivity and self-care?"
DESCRIPTION:For this workshop\, the common myth of productivity and self-
 efficacy will be discussed to help attendees&#160\;find out how to feel g
 ood about their work and projects. Plus\, there will be a discussion (or 
 self-discussion) about finding their own definition of rest and rejuvenat
 ion. Hye Ree earned her Doctor of Psychology (Psy.D.) degree in Clinical 
 Psychology with a focus on traumatic stress psychology from Adler Univers
 ity in Chicago. Hye Ree serves&#160\;as an embedded counselor&#160\;at th
 e ACC.&#160\;All Indiana University events\, groups\, activities\, and&#1
 60\;educational\, cultural\, and historical observances welcome all IU st
 udents and other members of the Indiana University community.For more inf
 ormation\, view this event in BeInvolved (https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/
 event/12168296).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">
 For this workshop\, the common myth of productivity and self-efficacy wil
 l be discussed to help attendees&#160\;find out how to feel good about th
 eir work and projects. Plus\, there will be a discussion (or self-discuss
 ion) about finding their own definition of rest and rejuvenation. Hye Ree
  earned her Doctor of Psychology (Psy.D.) degree in Clinical Psychology w
 ith a focus on traumatic stress psychology from Adler University in Chica
 go. Hye Ree serves&#160\;as an embedded counselor&#160\;at the ACC.</span
 >&#160\;</p><br /><p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">All Indiana
  University events\, groups\, activities\, and&#160\;educational\, cultur
 al\, and historical observances welcome all IU students and other members
  of the Indiana University community.</span></p><br /><strong>For more in
 formation\, <a href="https://beinvolved.indiana.edu/event/12168296">view 
 this event in BeInvolved</a>.</strong>
