DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Mentoring Services and Leadership Development \n\nT
 his MAP Session is the fifth out of six sessions for the Spring 2026 Semes
 ter. In this session\, we will talk about how to identify\, and prevent\, 
 burnout as a student leader.&nbsp\; The Mentor Apprenticeship Program (MAP
 ) is a two-semester training series facilitated by the FASE Mentoring Prog
 ram. It gives students at IU Bloomington opportunities to enhance their me
 ntoring\, teamwork\, and leadership skills.&nbsp\;Upon completion of MAP\,
  students receive a Certificate of Completion\, which establishes their co
 mmitment to growth and leadership. All Indiana University events\, groups\
 , activities\, and educational\, cultural\, and historical observances wel
 come all IU students and other members of the Indiana University community
 .
