SUMMARY: AlgoRhythms: AI\, Music\, and Human-Centered Creativity
DESCRIPTION:Indiana University Jacobs School of Music\, partnered with th
 e Maurer School of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, and the AI+Digi
 tal Futures Team\, presents AlgoRhythms 2026\, March 26–28 in Bloomington
  and online. This multi-day conference brings together artists\, scholars
 \, technologists\, educators\, and industry professionals to explore how 
 artificial intelligence is transforming music creation\, ownership\, and 
 the future of creative work.\n\nFriday\, March 27\n\n9:00 AM–5:00 PM — Mu
 sic Tech Playground\nAn interactive day of live demonstrations and conver
 sations showcasing emerging music technologies and creative tools.\nIU In
 novates | In Person Only\nSponsored by Sweetwater Sound\n\n6:00–8:00 PM —
  Reception\nAn evening gathering to connect with fellow attendees\, prese
 nters\, and collaborators.\nGraduate Bloomington | In Person Only\nSponso
 red by IU Office of the Chancellor\n\nSign up here https://forms.office.c
 om/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=NL4TEdGuAE2rS83QJRC-kdRT0NpCm_pFldrMPyyiXzV
 UMFRGSUg0V0lHV1BTTkJBSTVLOUFLUlRVMS4u&route=shorturl to attend either the
  in-person or virtual panel discussions.
