 6cd614-daae-4d91-8c78-b51460cbfb1a4f9e8115-2938-4e55-8eda-4b13f5166a38.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Pre-Physician Assistant Club at IU\n\nThe Pre-PA cl
 ub is conducting a phlebotomy course\, led by Nicholas Perrotta\, where he
  will teach pre-PA and other IU students valuable venipuncture skills. Upo
 n completion of the course\, the students will receive a phlebotomy certif
 ication lasting up to two years. The training length is 2 days\,&nbsp\;Sat
 urday\, March 28th and Sunday\, March 29th . &nbsp\;On Sunday\, clinic usu
 ally wraps up around 2:30pm\, with an optional discussion afterward about 
 strategies\, fielding questions about job/volunteer opportunities as a phl
 ebotomist\, etc. This is a challenging and rewarding clinic that will be o
 f great value students as they continue their health career.&nbsp\; "Nick&
 nbsp\;is a very experienced instructor (20+ years) who has not only been t
 eaching university students but also several hospitals&rsquo\; research st
 aff and county public health departments and he has a diverse research bac
 kground." Note:&nbsp\;Certification is valid anywhere in the United 
LOCATION:Global & International Studies\, GA 1100
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11912208
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
