UID:TKF/62fb9575b27fd5064283290f/2025/29578380/0/0
DTSTART:20260328T130000Z
DTEND:20260328T210000Z
URL:https://tockify.com/bloomington.arts.calendar/detail/2025/17747028000
 00
SUMMARY: AlgoRhythms: AI\, Music\, and Human-Centered Creativity
DESCRIPTION:Indiana University Jacobs School of Music\, partnered with th
 e Maurer School of Law\, IU Innovates\, Music Tectonics\, and the AI+Digi
 tal Futures Team\, presents AlgoRhythms 2026\, March 26–28 in Bloomington
  and online. This multi-day conference brings together artists\, scholars
 \, technologists\, educators\, and industry professionals to explore how 
 artificial intelligence is transforming music creation\, ownership\, and 
 the future of creative work.\n\nSaturday\, March 28\nAll events held in S
 weeney Hall at the Indiana University Jacobs School of Music | Also strea
 ming online\n\n9:00 AM — Business Transformation in the Music AI World\nA
  panel exploring how AI is reshaping the music industry\, from creation t
 o distribution and business strategy.\n\n10:30 AM — Emerging Tools and Cr
 eative Pathways in Music & AI\nA conversation highlighting new technologi
 es and evolving creative workflows for musicians and industry professiona
 ls.\n\n12:15 PM — Keynote Address\nA featured keynote examining innovatio
 n and future directions at the intersection of music and technology.\n\n2
 :00 PM — Creativity in AI: Artistic Migration & New Territories\nA discus
 sion on how AI is expanding artistic practice and opening new creative po
 ssibilities.\n\n4:00 PM — Creativity in AI: Understanding the Known & Unk
 nown\nA closing panel reflecting on current developments in AI music and 
 the questions still unfolding for artists and audiences.\n\nSign up here 
 https://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=NL4TEdGuAE2rS83QJRC-k
 dRT0NpCm_pFldrMPyyiXzVUMFRGSUg0V0lHV1BTTkJBSTVLOUFLUlRVMS4u&route=shortur
 l to attend either the in-person or virtual panel discussions.
CATEGORIES:
