X-SOURCE-URLS:{"CitySpark Bloomington": "http://www.eclipseproductionscompany.com"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_bloomington
SUMMARY:Rosencrantz and Guildenstern Are Dead by Tom Stoppard
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T193000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T215000
UID:260213VEX5_gICW0izagZ2--Fz6A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/6i1smXuOe0efQDr0u7wFMQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Acclaimed as a modern dramatic masterpiece\, Rosencrantz and G
 uildenstern Are Dead is the fabulously inventive tale of Hamlet as told fr
 om the worm's-eye view of the bewildered Rosencrantz and Guildenstern\, tw
 o minor characters in Shakespeare's play. In Tom Stoppard's best-known wor
 k\, this Shakespearean Laurel and Hardy finally get a chance to take the l
 ead role\, but do so in a world where echoes of Waiting for Godot resound\
 , where reality and illusion intermix\, and where fate leads our two heroe
 s to a tragic but inevitable end.
LOCATION:Constellation Playhouse
URL:http://www.eclipseproductionscompany.com
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
