 tml?Primarycode=140015">https://webtrac.bloomington.in.gov/webtrac/web/sear
 ch.html?Primarycode=140015</a>. For ages 18 yrs. and up.<br>Nobody can disc
 over the world for somebody else\, writes Kentucky author Wendell Berry. In
  this program we will tap into the inspiration the forest offers as we exam
 ine the relationship between poetry and place. As we hike through lovely Le
 onard Springs\, participants will have the opportunity to hear excerpts fro
 m multiple nature writers\, before stopping to write their own. One will ha
 ve the opportunity to share their writing\, or keep it private. Participant
 s will be given a nature notebook and pencil.
