 70103b-52bc-4df9-93c2-864e57c5487a76cd922a-632d-4895-bd68-4e519f32cd1e.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Office for Sexual Violence Prevention and Victim Ad
 vocacy\n\nThe&nbsp\;It&rsquo\;s&nbsp\;On&nbsp\;Us: Bystander Intervention 
 Workshop is a 90-minute\, audience-driven bystander intervention program t
 hat teaches students the skills needed to help in situations involving alc
 ohol and drug use that could lead to a sexual assault. Students practice h
 elping in real-life scenarios&nbsp\;and discuss how alcohol and drug use i
 nfluences a person&rsquo\;s ability to give and get consent to engage in s
 exual activity with another person.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; It's&nbsp\;On Us is&nbs
 p\; required &nbsp\;for all&nbsp\;first-year&nbsp\;and transfer undergradu
 ate students. &nbsp\; You must attend one session to fulfill the&nbsp\;req
 uirement.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; Instructions:&nbsp\; &nbsp\; Those who arrive mor
 e than 5 minutes after the start time will NOT be allowed into the session
  and will need to attend a different session &nbsp\; If this is your assig
 ned workshop but you cannot attend&nbsp\; it in its entirety \, please RSV
 P
LOCATION:Ballantine Hall\, room 006
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11969848
