X-SOURCE-ID:visitbloomington
SUMMARY:Pysanky Workshop with Natalie Kravchuk
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T040000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T035959Z
UID:event-58203@visitbloomington.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://assets.simpleviewinc.com/simpleview/imag
 e/upload/crm/bloomington/Screenshot-2026-03-04-at-2.08.50-PM_4711F612-0CED
 -B269-11235254E88540CF_471543e3-f84f-88cb-916c5dff7f37e4a7.png
DESCRIPTION:Join Pysanky artist Natalie Kravchuk and learn the folk art of
  Pysanka writing\, the decorating of eggs using wax and colored dyes\, as 
 has been practiced for thousands of years in Ukraine and other parts of Ea
 stern Europe. All supplies will be provided. You may work on as many eggs 
 as time allows. We will be working with hot wax and dyes\, so please dress
  accordingly. The cost is $30 per person and includes all materials. Open 
 to ages 9 and above. Children must be accompanied by an adult.
LOCATION:Pottery House Studio
URL:https://www.visitbloomington.com/event/pysanky-workshop-with-natalie-k
 ravchuk/58203/
X-SOURCE:Visit Bloomington
END:VEVENT
