SUMMARY:Taiwan Studies Initiative Milk Tea Month: Routes of Taiwan Tea
DESCRIPTION:From misty mountain oolongs to the global boba boom\, Taiwan'
 s teas carry far more than flavor. They embody contested borders\, evolvi
 ng identities\, and the complexities of nationhood. Dr. Hung's talk based
  on his newly published book\,Routes of Taiwan Tea\,traces tea varieties\
 , processing expertise\, and merchants across Taiwan and Southeast Asia t
 o reveal how a simple leaf has become a force in global politics.Lunch wi
 ll be provided.
