SUMMARY:April First Thursday at the Eskenazi Museum of Art
DESCRIPTION:Museum Activities for April First Thursday:4–7 p.m. Unwind 
 at the Museum    Live music and crafting celebrating featured exhibit Mul
 yana: Vital Ecosystems. (https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2123873-dr
 op-in-tours-and-crafting)&#160\;5 p.m. Artist Talk\,Rania Matar: Where Do
  I Go? لوين روح؟    Catch this special artist talk with photograp
 her Rania Matar\, who will share insights into her creative practice and 
 the powerful portraits. More info and RSVP here. (https://events.iu.edu/e
 vent/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-) (2nd Floor\, Martin 
 Commons)  5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, Listening to Coral Bones    Exp
 erience a live performance by dancer and performance artist Utam Moses\, 
 who brings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's sculptural c
 oral-inspired costume Form of Silence. The performance begins in the gall
 ery at 5:45 p.m. before moving out toward the Arts Plaza and the First Th
 ursday festival.  Special Giveaway: Tag the museum in a Mulyana: Vitaleco
 systems exhibition photo on social media for a giveaway item while suppli
 es last! (confirm post at giveaway station\, 1st floor atrium)  Newkirk G
 ift Shop Open (2ndFloor Atrium)Know Before You GoThis event is part of th
 e First Thursdays festivals showcase. (https://artsandhumanities.indiana.
 edu/council-programs/first-thursdays/index.html)Read aboutwhere to find u
 s\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.
