  Thursday:</strong></p><div id="lw_cal_event_detail_description" class="l
 w_cal_event_detail_block"><p><strong><span data-contrast="none">4–7 p.m
 . Unwind at the Museum</span></strong></p><p>    Live music and crafting 
 celebrating featured exhibit <em><a href="https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum
 /event/2123873-drop-in-tours-and-crafting" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
 >Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems.</a>&#160\;</em></p><p aria-level="2"><strong>
 <span data-contrast="none">5 p.m. Artist Talk\,</span><em>Rania Matar: Wh
 ere Do I Go? لوين روح؟</em></strong></p><p>    Catch this special
  artist talk with photographer Rania Matar\, who will share insights into
  her creative practice and the powerful portraits. <a href="https://event
 s.iu.edu/event/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-" target="_b
 lank" rel="noopener">More info and RSVP here.</a> (2nd Floor\, Martin Com
 mons)  </p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProofing
 "><strong>5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, <em>Listening to Coral Bones</e
 m></strong></p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProo
 fing">    Experience a live performance by dancer and performance artist 
 Utam Moses\, who brings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's
  sculptural coral-inspired costume <i>Form of Silence</i>. The performanc
 e begins in the gallery at 5:45 p.m. before moving out toward the Arts Pl
