X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eskenazi Museum of Art": "https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_eskenazi_museum
X-SOURCE:Eskenazi Museum of Art
DTSTART:20260402T210000Z
DTEND:20260402T223000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Artist Talk| Rania Matar: Where Do I Go? لوين روح؟
DESCRIPTION:5-6 p.m.Artist talk (2nd Floor\, Martin Commons)6-7 p.m. Exhi
 bition Visit (3rd Floor Gallery)About the Artist:  Matar was born and rai
 sed in Lebanon and moved to the U.S. in 1984. As a Lebanese-born\, Americ
 an/Palestinian woman and mother\, Matar's cultural background\, cross-cul
 tural experience\, and personal narrative inform her photography. She has
  dedicated her work to exploring issues of personal and collective identi
 ty\, through photographs of female adolescence and womanhood. She works b
 oth in the United States where she lives and the Middle East where she is
  from\, to focus on notions of identity and individuality all within the 
 context of the underlying universality of these experiences.About the Cur
 ator:  Elliot Josephine Leila Reichert is an American curator\, critic\, 
 and editor. She is the inaugural Curator of Contemporary Art at the Esken
 azi Museum of Art at Indiana University and was a 2023-24 Propel Fellow w
 ith the Association of Art Museum Curators Foundation. She was formerly A
 rt Editor of Newcity and Assistant Curator at the Block Museum of Art\, N
 orthwestern University. She has curated and assisted in developing critic
 ally celebrated exhibitions in the United States and abroad.    This even
 t is part of the First Thursdays festivals showcase. (https://artsandhuma
 nities.indiana.edu/council-programs/first-thursdays/index.html)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>5-6 p.m.</strong><strong>Artist t
 alk</strong> (2nd Floor\, Martin Commons)</p><p><strong>6-7 p.m. Exhibiti
 on Visit</strong> (3rd Floor Gallery)</p><p><strong>About the Artist:</st
 rong></p><p dir="ltr">  Matar was born and raised in Lebanon and moved to
  the U.S. in 1984. As a Lebanese-born\, American/Palestinian woman and mo
 ther\, Matar's cultural background\, cross-cultural experience\, and pers
 onal narrative inform her photography. She has dedicated her work to expl
 oring issues of personal and collective identity\, through photographs of
  female adolescence and womanhood. She works both in the United States wh
 ere she lives and the Middle East where she is from\, to focus on notions
  of identity and individuality all within the context of the underlying u
 niversality of these experiences.</p><p><span data-contrast="none"><stron
 g>About the Curator:</strong></span></p><p>  Elliot Josephine Leila Reich
 ert is an American curator\, critic\, and editor. She is the inaugural Cu
 rator of Contemporary Art at the Eskenazi Museum of Art at Indiana Univer
 sity and was a 2023-24 Propel Fellow with the Association of Art Museum C
 urators Foundation. She was formerly Art Editor of Newcity and Assistant 
 Curator at the Block Museum of Art\, Northwestern University. She has cur
 ated and assisted in developing critically celebrated exhibitions in the 
 United States and abroad.</p><div id="lw_cal_event_detail_description" cl
 ass="lw_cal_event_detail_block"><p>    This event is part of the <a class
 ="external" href="https://artsandhumanities.indiana.edu/council-programs/
 first-thursdays/index.html">First Thursdays festivals showcase.</a></p></
 div>
