SUMMARY:Special Event: A Conversation about U.S.-Taiwan Relations with Al
 exander Yui (Taiwan's Representative to the U.S.)
DESCRIPTION:The keynote and conversation Q&amp\;A with Representative Yui
  will take place from 2pm-3pm. The event will conclude with a musical per
 formance featuring IU Jacobs School faculty and students\, part of the IU
 -Taiwan Collaborations in Music Project\, followed by a reception for reg
 istered attendees in the Atrium.&#160\;  Alexander Tah-Ray Yui is Taiwan'
 s Representative to the United States\, a role he assumed in December 202
 3. He has over 35 years of experience in diplomacy and most recently serv
 ed as Taiwan's Representative to the European Union and Belgium and as Vi
 ce Minister of Foreign Affairs. Throughout his career\, he has worked to 
 expand Taiwan's global partnerships and strengthen its international pres
 ence. He has participated in executive education programs at UPenn\, LSE\
 , and Harvard.&#160\;  This special event is presented by the Hamilton Lu
 gar School\, the East Asian Studies Center\, the Taiwan Studies Initiativ
 e\, and the East Asia and the World speaker series.&#160\;
