 ith Representative Yui will take place from 2pm-3pm. The event will concl
 ude with a musical performance featuring IU Jacobs School faculty and stu
 dents\, part of the IU-Taiwan Collaborations in Music Project\, followed 
 by a reception for registered attendees in the Atrium.&#160\;</p><p>  Ale
 xander Tah-Ray Yui is Taiwan's Representative to the United States\, a ro
 le he assumed in December 2023. He has over 35 years of experience in dip
 lomacy and most recently served as Taiwan's Representative to the Europea
 n Union and Belgium and as Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs. Throughout h
 is career\, he has worked to expand Taiwan's global partnerships and stre
 ngthen its international presence. He has participated in executive educa
 tion programs at UPenn\, LSE\, and Harvard.&#160\;</p><p>  This special e
 vent is presented by the Hamilton Lugar School\, the East Asian Studies C
 enter\, the Taiwan Studies Initiative\, and the East Asia and the World s
 peaker series.&#160\;</p>
