X-SOURCE-ID:visitbloomington
SUMMARY:13th Annual Indiana University Traditional Pow Wow
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T040000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260405T035959Z
UID:event-58106@visitbloomington.com
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://assets.simpleviewinc.com/simpleview/imag
 e/upload/crm/bloomington/Pow-Wow_6B3E4118-D084-123A-E51B29DFAC2EFA64_6b5b9
 f0c-d292-a598-c1d1cde5215b0fed.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The modern powwow and many styles of contemporary powwow danci
 ng have their roots in the historic warrior societies of the Southern and 
 Northern Plains. Over time\, these dances\, ceremonies\, and gatherings ha
 ve evolved from formal\, tribal-based ceremonies into modern-day intertrib
 al celebrations of culture\, dance\, song\, crafts\, food\, and pageantry.
  Protocol: Attendees are encouraged to respect elders\, not touch dancers'
  regalia\, and walk around the dance circle.
LOCATION:Wilkinson Hall
URL:https://www.visitbloomington.com/event/13th-annual-indiana-university-
 traditional-pow-wow/58106/
X-SOURCE:Visit Bloomington
END:VEVENT
