BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sycamore Land Trust": "https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/fire-on-the-landscape-with-sam-shoaf/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:sycamore_land_trust
SUMMARY:Fire on the Landscape with Sam Shoaf
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T120000
UID:35142d811bd1c1f3a93d2669a5a40101@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:The whippoorwill\, a species of concern here in Indiana\, has 
 found safe refuge in the recently burned areas of Downey Hill\, but why? J
 oin us for a guided hike through the Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey 
 Hill with Sam Shoaf\, Director of Operations and Burn Boss at Eco Logic\, 
 LLC\, to explore the vital role of fire in Indiana’s ecosystems. Sam wil
 l share insights into how prescribed burns are planned and conducted\, and
  how fire helps maintain healthy forests\, promote native plant growth\, a
 nd support wildlife diversity. Participants will walk through areas recent
 ly shaped by fire and learn how this natural process contributes to long-t
 erm habitat restoration and resilience.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/fire-on-the-landscape-with-sam-s
 hoaf/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
