 n the first floor
SUMMARY:Writing in the Galleries: Where Do I Go?
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, we begin by looking closely at artwork—a
 sking what we see\, think\, feel\, and wonder. Together\, we'll explore t
 he artist's possible message and its social meaning\, then turn those ref
 lections into our own creative responses.  Whether you're a writer or sim
 ply curious to try something new\, you'll find inspiration here and a wel
 coming community to share the journey.  About the Exhibition  Step into t
 he world of acclaimed photographer Rania Matar (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whos
 e striking portraits document young women persisting in uncertain times. 
 Matar's lens highlights women's creativity\, strength\, dignity\, and res
 ilience—offering a powerful counter-narrative to the challenges of her 
 country and region. Read more about this featured exhibition (https://art
 museum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_feature-exhibitions/2026-03-05-r
 ania-matar-where-do-i-go.html).  What to Bringyour favorite pencil (no pe
 ns).  a notebook or paper. Clipboards are available to borrow.  a phone o
 r camera to take a picture of the art for later reference.  Know Before Y
 ou GoArrive early\, check in\, and get ready for an on-time start.Readwhe
 re to find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.Abo
 ut Your Facilitator  Dedaimia Whitney earned an MFA in fiction from India
 na University under the direction of Scott Russell Sanders. She taught cr
 eative writing at Franklin College for many years. She has served the mus
 eum as a docent since 2019. Her favorite works of art are those that are 
 both visually stimulating and thought-provoking.
