SUMMARY:External Moot Court Competition info session
DESCRIPTION:This is event is for all rising 2Ls and 3Ls interested in com
 peting in an external (intermural) moot court competition during the 2026
 -2027 school year. Professor McFadden will explain what some of those com
 petitions are\, what they require\, and how to apply. This event is NOT a
 bout the 2L Sherman Minton Moot Court Competition\, for which there is a 
 separate information session on March 31.  Most competitions require that
  competitors be enrolled in a full-time JD program. 3L students with Sher
 man Minton or other moot court experience will be preferred when selectin
 g teams\, but each year we do send highly competitive 2Ls to national com
 petitions\, so all interested students are encouraged to attend. Applicat
 ions for all 2026-2027 teams will be due by April 17.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This is event is for all rising 2Ls and
  3Ls interested in competing in an external (intermural) moot court compe
 tition during the 2026-2027 school year. Professor McFadden will explain 
 what some of those competitions are\, what they require\, and how to appl
 y. This event is NOT about the 2L Sherman Minton Moot Court Competition\,
  for which there is a separate information session on March 31.</p><p>  M
 ost competitions require that competitors be enrolled in a full-time JD p
 rogram. 3L students with Sherman Minton or other moot court experience wi
 ll be preferred when selecting teams\, but each year we do send highly co
 mpetitive 2Ls to national competitions\, so all interested students are e
 ncouraged to attend. Applications for all 2026-2027 teams will be due by 
 April 17.&#160\;</p>
