SUMMARY:Common Threads
DESCRIPTION:Looking for a welcoming space to crochet\, knit\, embroider\,
  quilt\, and explore other fiber arts? Interested in sharing your experie
 nces and connecting with others while learning new skills? Or even just w
 ant a place to vent while you work on your scarf you've been crocheting f
 or 2 years? Look no further\; join us for Common Threads!  Common Threads
  is a free program open to the public and offers a welcoming environment 
 to share\, unwind\, and learn! You can bring your own fiber art to work o
 n while working alongside others who enjoy working in fiber and textiles.
  Or you can try learning something new\; we welcome all skill levels! Eit
 her way\, you're sure to have a good time.  This group meets on the 1st a
 nd 3rd Tuesday of each month from 3–4:30 p.m.\, excluding holidays and 
 museum closures. The group will meet in the Roehm Family Art-making Studi
 o\, located inside the Simpson Center for Education on the 2nd floor of t
 he Eskenazi Museum of Art.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Looking for a welcoming space to croche
 t\, knit\, embroider\, quilt\, and explore other fiber arts? Interested i
 n sharing your experiences and connecting with others while learning new 
 skills? Or even just want a place to vent while you work on your scarf yo
 u've been crocheting for 2 years? Look no further\; join us for Common Th
 reads!</p><p>  Common Threads is a free program open to the public and of
 fers a welcoming environment to share\, unwind\, and learn! You can bring
  your own fiber art to work on while working alongside others who enjoy w
 orking in fiber and textiles. Or you can try learning something new\; we 
 welcome all skill levels! Either way\, you're sure to have a good time.</
 p><p>  This group meets on the 1st and 3rd Tuesday of each month from 3
 4:30 p.m.\, excluding holidays and museum closures. The group will meet 
 in the Roehm Family Art-making Studio\, located inside the Simpson Center
  for Education on the 2nd floor of the Eskenazi Museum of Art.</p>
