X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eskenazi Museum of Art": "https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2101228-homeschool-day-map-making"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_eskenazi_museum
X-SOURCE:Eskenazi Museum of Art
DTSTART:20260409T140000Z
DTEND:20260409T160000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Map Making
DESCRIPTION:Students will explore paintings of landscapes and landmarks i
 n the galleries\, then imagine themselves as travelers journeying to new 
 lands. Back in the studio\, we'll ask questions about territories\, terra
 ins\, and landmarks\, as we design and create our own imaginative maps.Kn
 ow Before You Go:  Meet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 10 a.m. Toge
 ther\, we'll drop off personal items in the Simpson Center for Education 
 before exploring the galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire o
 ur project\, we'll head back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to cre
 ate our own masterpieces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!  Strollers ar
 e welcome. Chaperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, w
 ith one adult for every 6 children.Parking Information:  The museum is in
  the pedestrian district of campus with several parking options nearby. T
 he Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is just a 5-minute walk
  diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% off parking valida
 tion at the museum's guest services desk. The East Garage (105 N. Eagleso
 n Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also convenient\, about
  an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the Bloomington campu
 s here (https://parking.indiana.edu/facilities/index.html).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Students will explore paintings of land
 scapes and landmarks in the galleries\, then imagine themselves as travel
 ers journeying to new lands. Back in the studio\, we'll ask questions abo
 ut territories\, terrains\, and landmarks\, as we design and create our o
 wn imaginative maps.</p><p><strong>Know Before You Go:</strong></p><p>  M
 eet us on the 1st floor of the museum at 10 a.m. Together\, we'll drop of
 f personal items in the Simpson Center for Education before exploring the
  galleries. After seeing artworks that will inspire our project\, we'll h
 ead back to the Roehm Family Art-Making Studio to create our own masterpi
 eces! Don't forget to dress for a mess!</p><p>  Strollers are welcome. Ch
 aperones required. We ask that chaperones be 18 or older\, with one adult
  for every 6 children.</p><p><strong>Parking Information:</strong></p><p>
   The museum is in the pedestrian district of campus with several parking
  options nearby. The Indiana Memorial Union lot (900 E. 7th Street) is ju
 st a 5-minute walk diagonal to the museum\, and visitors can receive 40% 
 off parking validation at the museum's guest services desk. The East Gara
 ge (105 N. Eagleson Ave.) and Fee Lane Garage (709 N. Fee Lane) are also 
 convenient\, about an 8–10 minute walk. Learn more about parking on the
  Bloomington campus <a class="external" href="https://parking.indiana.edu
 /facilities/index.html">here</a>.</p>
UID:20260409T140000Z-2101228@events.iu.edu
