X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Cinema": "https://events.iu.edu/cinemaiub/event/2226337-black-snow-wfilmmaker-in-light-human-rights-document"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_cinema
X-SOURCE:IU Cinema
DTSTART:20260411T200000Z
DTEND:20260411T210000Z
LOCATION:IU CINEMA
GEO:39.168613;-86.517376
SUMMARY:Black Snow w/filmmaker | In Light Human Rights Documentary Film F
 estival
DESCRIPTION:Siberian homemaker-turned-journalist Natalia Zubkova uncovers
  a toxic mine fire poisoning her remote coal town's homes with deadly gas
 es. As her viral reporting exposes government corruption and the coal maf
 ia\, she faces surveillance\, harassment\, and threats from an authoritar
 ian regime. This courageous mother battles for environmental justice in a
  polluted world of black snow. [96 min\; documentary\; Russian with Engli
 sh subtitles]A Zoom Q&amp\;A with filmmaker Alina Simone and Dr. Andy Bru
 no (Stephen F. Cohen Chair of Russian History\, IU Dept. of History) will
  follow the screening.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Siberian homemaker-turned-journalist Na
 talia Zubkova uncovers a toxic mine fire poisoning her remote coal town's
  homes with deadly gases. As her viral reporting exposes government corru
 ption and the coal mafia\, she faces surveillance\, harassment\, and thre
 ats from an authoritarian regime. This courageous mother battles for envi
 ronmental justice in a polluted world of black snow. [96 min\; documentar
 y\; Russian with English subtitles]</p><p><i><strong>A Zoom Q&amp\;A with
  filmmaker Alina Simone and Dr. Andy Bruno (Stephen F. Cohen Chair of Rus
 sian History\, IU Dept. of History) will follow the screening.</strong></
 i></p>
