DTSTART:20260413T160000Z
DTEND:20260413T173000Z
LOCATION:The Ostrom Workshop\, 513 N PARK AVE - Room Number: Tocqueville
GEO:39.171057;-86.524959
SUMMARY:Ostrom Workshop | Colloquium: Brandice Canes-Wrone
DESCRIPTION:About the Colloquium SeriesEach Monday throughout the academi
 c year\, speakers share and discuss cutting edge research echoing the the
 mes of the Ostrom Workshop's research program. Topics range from the gove
 rnance of space\, cybersecurity\, and data management\, to the environmen
 t\, political economy\, and sustainable food science. Presenters are from
  IU and around the world. Join us at the workshop or over Zoom to learn h
 ow the Ostrom legacy is evolving today. For more information\, see ourweb
 site (https://ostromworkshop.indiana.edu/index.html). Meeting URL: https:
 //iu.zoom.us/j/86442029094
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong><span data-contrast="none">About 
 the Colloquium Series</span></strong><span data-ccp-props="{&quot\;134233
 117&quot\;:true\,&quot\;134233118&quot\;:true\,&quot\;201341983&quot\;:0\
 ,&quot\;335559685&quot\;:720\,&quot\;335559740&quot\;:240}"></span></p><p
 ><span data-contrast="none">Each Monday throughout the academic year\, sp
 eakers share and discuss cutting edge research echoing the themes of the 
 Ostrom Workshop's research program. Topics range from the governance of s
 pace\, cybersecurity\, and data management\, to the environment\, politic
 al economy\, and sustainable food science. Presenters are from IU and aro
 und the world. Join us at the workshop or over Zoom to learn how the Ostr
 om legacy is evolving today. For more information\, see our</span><span d
 ata-contrast="none"><a href="https://ostromworkshop.indiana.edu/index.htm
 l" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website</a></span><span data-contrast="
 none">.</span></p> Meeting URL: https://iu.zoom.us/j/86442029094
