SUMMARY:Recovery Ally Training
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T180000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T193000Z
UID:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12164957
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://se-images.campuslabs.com/clink/images/2f
 3fff29-c267-4789-92bd-eb4ee3f840d24fcb9b09-c7e7-495c-8181-ca634fef4015.png
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: Collegiate Recovery Community\n\nRecovery Ally Trai
 ning is an interactive educational workshop designed to increase awareness
 \, reduce stigma\, and build practical skills to support individuals in re
 covery from substance use disorders. Participants will learn about recover
 y pathways\, common challenges faced by people in recovery\, and how langu
 age\, policies\, and everyday interactions can either support or hinder re
 covery efforts. This training emphasizes empathy\, inclusivity\, and actio
 nable strategies\, empowering participants to serve as visible\, informed 
 allies within their communities\, workplaces\, or campuses. By the end of 
 the training\, attendees will have a stronger understanding of recovery-or
 iented practices and how to create safer\, more supportive environments fo
 r people in recovery.
LOCATION:Wellness House 115
URL:https://iub.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12164957
X-SOURCE:IU beINvolved Student Orgs
END:VEVENT
