BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"IU Hamilton Lugar School": "https://events.iu.edu/live/events/2169244-book-talk-the-permanence-of-anti-roma-racism"}
X-SOURCE-ID:iu_hamilton_lugar
X-SOURCE:IU Hamilton Lugar School
DTSTART:20260420T180000Z
DTEND:20260420T190000Z
LOCATION:GLOBAL &amp\; INTERNATIONAL STUDIES BUILDING - Room Number: 4067
GEO:39.170002;-86.517492
SUMMARY:Book Talk: "The Permanence of anti-Roma Racism: (Un)uttered Sente
 nces" With Margareta Matache
DESCRIPTION:This talk draws on Margareta Matache's new book\,The Permanen
 ce of anti-Roma Racism: (Un)uttered Sentences\, to examine anti-Roma raci
 sm\, which she frames in Romani as ofitsialo telćhudipen (structural or 
 top-down oppression). The focus will include the origins\, protectors\, l
 egacies\, and continuities of anti-Roma racism\, as well as its place wit
 hin global frameworks and theories related to oppression\, racism\, racia
 lization\, and slavery.Margareta Matache\, PhD\, is a Harvard Lecturer\, 
 co-founder\, and Director of the Roma Program at Harvard University. Mata
 che is the co-editor of Time for Reparations: A Global Perspective (2021)
  and Realizing Roma Rights (2017). Her most recent book\,The Permanence o
 f Anti-Roma Racism: (Un)uttered Sentences (Routledge)\, examines anti-Rom
 a racism and links to other oppressions.&#160\;  This event is cosponsore
 d by The Byrnes Institute\, the Institute for European Studies\, and the 
 Department of Anthropology
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-olk-copy-source="MessageBody">
 This talk draws on Margareta Matache's new book\,<i></i></span><i>The Per
 manence of anti-Roma Racism: (Un)uttered Sentences</i>\, to examine anti-
 Roma racism\, which she frames in Romani as <i>ofitsialo telćhudipen</i>
  (structural or top-down oppression). The focus will include the origins\
 , protectors\, legacies\, and continuities of anti-Roma racism\, as well 
 as its place within global frameworks and theories related to oppression\
 , racism\, racialization\, and slavery.</p><p><span data-olk-copy-source=
 "MessageBody">Margareta Matache\, PhD\, is a Harvard Lecturer\, co-founde
 r\, and Director of the Roma Program at Harvard University. Matache is th
 e co-editor of Time for Reparations: A Global Perspective (2021) and Real
 izing Roma Rights (2017). Her most recent book\,</span><i>The Permanence 
 of Anti-Roma Racism: (Un)uttered Sentences (Routledge)\,</i> examines ant
 i-Roma racism and links to other oppressions.&#160\;</p><p>  This event i
 s cosponsored by The Byrnes Institute\, the Institute for European Studie
 s\, and the Department of Anthropology</p>
