 ly Art-making Studio
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:DIY Metal Pour Workshop
DESCRIPTION:During this workshop\, attendees will learn about the Sculptu
 re Trails Outdoor Museum\, see examples of lost-wax and relief sculptures
  in the Eskenazi Museum of Art's collection\, and will be walked through 
 how to carve a relief sculpture on a provided "scratch block." Leading th
 e carving workshop are Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum staff Laura Gonzal
 ez (Outreach Coordinator) and Ethan Harmon (Artist-in-Residence)\, as wel
 l as Eskenazi Museum of Art's resident Arts-based Wellness Experiences Ma
 nager\, Keaton Evans-Black.PLEASE NOTE: Your scratch block will be taken 
 to the Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum to be completed through their meta
 l pour process. During the workshop\, you must schedule to retrieve your 
 artwork from either the Eskenazi Museum of Art or the Sculpture Trails Ou
 tdoor Museum at a later date.For more information about the Sculpture Tra
 ils Outdoor Museum\, click here. (https://sculpturetrails.com/about/)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="white">Duri
 ng this workshop\, attendees will learn about the Sculpture Trails Outdoo
 r Museum\, see examples of lost-wax and relief sculptures in the Eskenazi
  Museum of Art's collection\, and will be walked through how to carve a r
 elief sculpture on a provided "scratch block." Leading the carving worksh
 op are Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum staff Laura Gonzalez (Outreach Coo
 rdinator) and Ethan Harmon (Artist-in-Residence)\, as well as Eskenazi Mu
 seum of Art's resident Arts-based Wellness Experiences Manager\, Keaton E
 vans-Black.</span></p><p><span data-ogsc="" data-ogsb="white">PLEASE NOTE
 : Your scratch block will be taken to the Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum
  to be completed through their metal pour process. During the workshop\, 
 you must schedule to retrieve your artwork from either the Eskenazi Museu
 m of Art or the Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum at a later date.</span></
 p><p><span data-ogsc="black" data-ogsb="white">For more information about
  the Sculpture Trails Outdoor Museum\, <a href="https://sculpturetrails.c
 om/about/">click here.</a></span></p>
