 .html?Primarycode=140016</a>. For ages 10 yrs. and up.<br>Late spring-early
  summer is an excellent time to observe moths. These insects overwinter in 
 a pupal case under the leaf litter\, and arise in the springtime as beautif
 ul moths. Spring is the season when you are most likely to find cecropia an
 d luna moths. Lets see what we can find! Participants should plan to bring 
 portable seating and a flashlight and be able to hike on a moderate trail.
