SUMMARY: Another Revolution
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Another Revolution\,” 
 on stage June 4-21 at the Constellation Playhouse.\n\nSome revolutions ha
 ppen in the streets. Others in the lab.\n\nKat and Henry\, two graduate s
 tudents from opposing scientific disciplines\, are forced to share a lab 
 at Columbia University in 1968. Amidst interpersonal differences\, a camp
 us devolving into political chaos\, and the uncertainty and turmoil of th
 e outside world\, they each discover what it’s like to be thrown into som
 eone else’s orbit. By Jacqueline Bircher\, playwright of Constellation’s 
 hit production of Webster’s B!+@#. Recommended for ages 13+.\n\n\nSee Con
 stellation’s website for more information\, including a detailed performa
 nce schedule. Learn more and find tickets at seeconstellation.org/mainsta
 ge/another-revolution/ https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/another-rev
 olution/ https://seeconstellation.org/mainstage/another-revolution/
CATEGORIES:
